        "\n",
        "## Something Additional: Visualizing the Wage Distribution Shift\n",
        "\n",
        "One of the most compelling pieces of evidence in the paper is **Figure 1**: the\n",
        "distribution of starting wages in NJ and PA before and after the minimum wage increase.\n",
        "The paper only shows this as a histogram — here we recreate and extend it to make\n",
        "the Diff-in-Diff logic visually intuitive.\n",
        "\n",
        "The key insight: if the minimum wage is truly *binding* (i.e., it forced real wage\n",
        "changes), we should see NJ's wage distribution shift dramatically toward \\$5.05 after\n",
        "April 1992, while PA's distribution stays flat. This is exactly what happened — and\n",
        "it's the \"first stage\" that validates the whole study."
      ],
